/	: root directory
/bin	: executable programs
/etc	: configuration file 
/usr	: subdirectories,files,documentation
/boot	: files to boot Linux kernel
/dev	: device file for physical device
/home	: local user home directories
/media	: mounting device in file system tree
/mnt	: mounting device in file system tree
/lib	: shared lib used by /boot,/bin,/sbin
/lib64	: shared lib used by /boot,/bin,/sbin
/opt	: dir for optional packages
/proc	: dir for kernel information
/root	: home dir of root 
/run	: process and user information
/sbin	: just like /bin but of commands for sysadmin  
/srv	: dir for services like NFS,HTTP,FTP
/sys	: Manage kernel and associated process to provide interface to device
/tmp	: temporary files
/var	: log files,mail files ,spool files 

